## Friction Report (Honest Assessment)

The friction report must give ACTIONABLE engineering estimates:

### Estimation Rules:
| Condition | Hours Impact | Difficulty Impact |
|-----------|-------------|------------------|
| Full OpenAPI spec available | -16h | → Low |
| SDK in target language available | -8h | → Low |
| No API docs at all | +40h | → High |
| No authentication docs | +8h | +1 level |
| Complex auth (OAuth 2.0 + MFA) | +16h | +1 level |
| No webhook support | +8h (need polling) | — |
| Rate limiting undocumented | +8h (need discovery) | — |
| On-premise deployment only | +24h | → High |
| Multiple microservice dependencies | +16h per service | +1 level |

### Output must include:
```json
{
  "friction_report": {
    "overall_difficulty": "Low/Medium/High/Unknown",
    "estimated_hours": {
      "minimum": 16,
      "likely": 40,
      "maximum": 80,
      "breakdown": {
        "api_integration": 16,
        "authentication": 8,
        "data_mapping": 8,
        "testing": 8,
        "documentation_reverse_engineering": 0
      }
    },
    "blockers": ["No public API — may require partnership agreement"],
    "accelerators": ["REST API available", "Python SDK published on PyPI"],
    "risk_factors": [
      {
        "risk": "API stability unknown — no versioning policy found",
        "impact": "High — breaking changes could disrupt integration",
        "mitigation": "Implement adapter pattern with version abstraction"
      }
    ]
  }
}
```

